IX-Vahdat
Copyright 2026 Bryce Lovell

IX-Vahdat is a humanitarian water-resilience proof-of-concept released under
the Apache License, Version 2.0.

This repository provides software decision-support structures for evidence
gates, water-use classification, atmospheric-water triage, energy accounting,
maintenance readiness, infrastructure-health review, emergency reserve
protection, managed aquifer recharge screening, receipts, evidence bundles,
BOM planning, and human review.

IX-Vahdat does not certify water as potable, approve public distribution,
replace licensed public-health review, replace licensed engineering review,
issue permits, authorize construction, authorize discharge, authorize managed
aquifer recharge, or control physical systems autonomously.

Synthetic examples, demo payloads, estimated cost ranges, and generated
receipts are not field evidence and must not be presented as real deployment
records.
